## Screening Criteria
- **direct** (relevance_score ≥ 0.6): Paper directly addresses the survey topic
- **adjacent** (0.3–0.6): Paper addresses a related field that meaningfully informs the topic
- **foundational** (0.2–0.5): Paper provides essential background theory or methods
- **exclude** (<0.3 OR off-topic): Paper is not relevant, even if high quality

## Hard Rules
- REJECT papers about unrelated domains even if they are high quality
- REJECT papers that only tangentially mention the topic in passing
- REJECT papers published before 2015 unless they are seminal foundational works
- INCLUDE papers from adjacent fields ONLY if they directly inform methodology or theory

